## 2026-06-10 - Codex remediation for high-risk audit findings

- Remediated a focused high-risk slice from `CODE-REVIEW-2026-06-10.md` and
  deployed a verified local build to `/Applications/Engram.app`.
- Fixed areas:
  - Resume/launch: Codex now uses the `resume` subcommand, CLI discovery uses
    common shell binary paths, Ghostty runs composite commands through `zsh -lc`,
    and the app carries the Apple Events entitlement/usage string.
  - Runtime/IPC: frame deadlines now honor long request timeouts instead of
    imposing an unconditional 30s ceiling.
  - Date parsing/UI metrics: shared `EngramTimestampParser` covers whole,
    millisecond, microsecond, and SQLite-style timestamps; timeline bucketing and
    source-health KPIs use it.
  - AI generation: title regeneration no longer skips existing generated
    titles, keyless Ollama/custom title providers are accepted, summary protocol
    UI no longer advertises unsupported Anthropic/Gemini modes, and equivalent
    reindexing preserves existing AI summaries.
  - Read paths: Latin keyword search is FTS-driven instead of correlated
    per-session probes; replay timeline reads SQLite/FTS rows instead of an empty
    filesystem stub.
  - Ingestion/project move: startup scans all adapters, Kimi status-update token
    usage accumulates, project-move compensation only reverses a completed
    physical move, and same-slug Gemini moves update `projects.json`.
  - UI/observability: Sessions/Timeline suggested-child buttons call the service;
    OSLog reading requests system scope and maps `.error` to `error`.
- Verification:
  - Targeted Swift tests passed across `EngramServiceCore`, `EngramCoreTests`,
    and `EngramTests` for the fixes above.
  - `macos/scripts/build-release.sh --local-only` succeeded and verified
    Developer ID signing, hardened runtime, secure timestamp, helper structure,
    and bundle hygiene.
  - `macos/scripts/deploy-local.sh macos/build/EngramExport/Engram.app`
    installed `/Applications/Engram.app` build `20260610065205`; installed
    codesign verification passed and Apple Events entitlement is present.
- Residual risk:
  - Full `EngramServiceCore` scheme test was manually stopped after about 5m18s
    of repeated Xcode beta CoreDevice/CoreSimulator launch warnings with no
    explicit test failure observed.
  - This was a focused remediation pass, not closure of all 88 confirmed audit
    findings; the remaining medium/low findings and 8 unverified carryovers
    still need separate adjudication.

## 2026-06-10 - Multi-expert audit (security dimension excluded)

- Full-repo read-only audit: 11 domain experts + adversarial verification
  (272 subagents, two passes; first pass hit the monthly spend limit and was
  resumed from the workflow journal).
- Results: 88 confirmed findings (26 high / 50 medium / 12 low, 0 critical),
  9 refuted, 1 disputed, 8 UNVERIFIED carryovers (lost to the interruption,
  e.g. stale SessionCostPricing table -> cost_usd=0 for current models).
- Report: `CODE-REVIEW-2026-06-10.md`; summary in CHANGELOG.md [Unreleased].
  Hotspots: EngramService/Core, EngramCoreWrite/Indexing, Engram/Views.
- Systemic themes: per-view ad-hoc ISO8601 parsing; 30s IPC frame deadline vs
  long commands; sessions_fts.session_id UNINDEXED full scans; AI generation
  pipeline inert in default config; resume/launch surface broken end-to-end;
  tests that cannot fail (source-string asserts, TS-generated fixture DB).
- STANDING USER PREFERENCE: do NOT include a security/vulnerability expert in
  multi-agent reviews of this repo (risk-control false triggers); state "no
  security analysis" in reviewer prompts. No findings fixed as of 2026-06-10.

