## 2026-06-06 — Project move covers Codex rollout summaries (Codex)

Codex closed a remaining project-move compatibility gap for Codex-derived
durable memory artifacts.

Finding:
- Real local Codex session history uses flat JSONL stores under
  `~/.codex/sessions` and `~/.codex/archived_sessions`; those were already
  covered by project-move roots.
- The local Codex memory layout also has
  `~/.codex/memories/rollout_summaries`, which can contain exported rollout
  JSONL with `session_meta` / `turn_context` cwd and workspace-root fields.
  Project move did not scan it, so moves could leave stale cwd references in
  Codex-derived memory summaries.
- `~/.codex/session_index.jsonl` samples contained ids, thread names, and
  timestamps, not cwd. `~/.codex/history.jsonl` contains raw prompt history and
  may mention paths, but it is not treated as session truth for project moves.

Change:
- `src/core/project-move/sources.ts` adds a flat
  `codex-rollout-summaries` source root at
  `~/.codex/memories/rollout_summaries`.
- `macos/EngramCoreWrite/ProjectMove/Sources.swift` mirrors the same source
  id and path for the Swift product pipeline.
- TS and Swift project-move tests now assert source-root parity and verify the
  orchestrator patches rollout-summary JSONL alongside active and archived
  Codex sessions.

Verification:
- RED: `npx vitest run tests/core/project-move/sources.test.ts
  tests/core/project-move/orchestrator.integration.test.ts` failed because
  `codex-rollout-summaries` was absent and the rollout-summary fixture still
  contained the old cwd.
- GREEN: the same targeted Vitest command passed 44 tests after adding the
  root.
- GREEN: `xcodebuild test -project macos/Engram.xcodeproj -scheme
  EngramCoreTests -destination 'platform=macOS'
  -only-testing:EngramCoreTests/SessionSourcesTests/testRootsReturnsCanonicalRootsInOrder`
  passed.
- GREEN: `xcodebuild test -project macos/Engram.xcodeproj -scheme
  EngramCoreTests -destination 'platform=macOS'
  -only-testing:EngramCoreTests/OrchestratorTests/testAllCodexStoresArePatchedAndCommitted`
  passed.

## 2026-06-06 — Gemini CLI projects cache refresh (Codex)

Codex closed the still-current P3 Gemini CLI `projectsCache` refresh finding.

Change:
- `src/adapters/gemini-cli.ts` now keys the in-memory `projects.json` cache by
  the file's `size:mtimeMs:ctimeMs` signature.
- `resolveProject()` keeps the cheap cache hit when `projects.json` is
  unchanged, but reloads when Gemini rewrites the file so long-running Engram
  processes resolve project slugs to the current cwd.
- Oversized, missing, or invalid `projects.json` inputs still resolve to an
  empty map and are cached by the observed signature to avoid repeated reads.

Verification:
- RED: `npx vitest run tests/adapters/gemini-cli.test.ts` failed because the
  second `resolveProject('my-project')` returned `/Users/test/old-project`
  after the fixture `projects.json` had been rewritten.
- GREEN: `npx vitest run tests/adapters/gemini-cli.test.ts` passed 11 tests.
- GREEN: `npx vitest run tests/adapters/gemini-cli.test.ts
  tests/adapters/antigravity.test.ts tests/adapters/edge-cases.test.ts`
  passed 30 tests.
- After subagent review flagged the same-size/same-mtime stale-cache edge, a
  RED source guard failed until `ctimeMs` became part of the signature.
- GREEN: `npx biome check --write src/adapters/gemini-cli.ts
  tests/adapters/gemini-cli.test.ts` passed with no fixes.
- GREEN: `npm run typecheck:test` passed.

## 2026-06-06 — TypeScript generate_summary MCP status semantics (Codex)

Codex closed the still-current `generate_summary` MCP `isError` misuse
finding.

Change:
- `src/tools/generate_summary.ts` now returns structured non-error status
  results for deterministic business outcomes:
  `not_found`, `not_configured`, `unsupported_source`, `empty`, and
  `empty_response`.
- Real execution failures, including transcript read failures and AI client
  exceptions, still return `isError: true`, now with
  `structuredContent.error.message`.
- `src/index.ts` maps daemon-routed `/api/summary` business rejections back to
  the same non-error status shape instead of reporting them as MCP errors.
- `tests/tools/generate_summary.test.ts` covers direct handler status results,
  retained error behavior, and daemon HTTP error mapping.

Verification:
- RED: `npx vitest run tests/tools/generate_summary.test.ts` failed 8 tests on
  the old implementation because business statuses returned `isError: true`,
  read errors lacked `structuredContent`, and the daemon mapper did not exist.
- GREEN: `npx vitest run tests/tools/generate_summary.test.ts` passed 8 tests.
- GREEN: `npx vitest run tests/tools/generate_summary.test.ts
  tests/web/daemon-http-contract.test.ts tests/web/server.test.ts` passed 91
  tests.
- GREEN: `npx biome check --write src/tools/generate_summary.ts src/index.ts
  tests/tools/generate_summary.test.ts` passed with no fixes.
- GREEN: `npm run typecheck:test` passed.

## 2026-06-06 — TypeScript database statement wrapper without Proxy (Codex)

Codex closed a still-current P1 TypeScript database instrumentation finding.

Change:
- `src/core/db/database.ts` replaces the `Proxy`-based prepared-statement
  instrumentation with a pre-bound wrapper object.
- The wrapper exposes stable own `run`, `get`, `all`, and `iterate` methods
  that record `db.query_ms`.
- Statement chain methods (`pluck`, `expand`, `raw`, `bind`, `safeIntegers`)
  call the underlying statement and return the wrapper, so chained calls keep
  metrics instrumentation instead of falling back to the raw statement.

Verification:
- RED: `npx vitest run tests/core/db.test.ts -t "instrumented statement"`
  failed because `get/run/all` were not own pre-bound wrappers.
- RED: `npx vitest run tests/core/db.test.ts -t "chain methods"` failed
  because `pluck().get()` recorded no histogram calls.
- GREEN: targeted RED tests passed after the fix.
- GREEN: `npx vitest run tests/core/db.test.ts` passed 55 tests.
- GREEN: `npm run typecheck:test` passed.
- GREEN: `git diff --check` passed.

Residual risk:
- This intentionally keeps instrumentation scoped to `Database.setMetrics()`
  prepared statements. Existing direct use of `db.raw` before metrics setup is
  unchanged.

