## 2026-06-06 — TypeScript migration_log state/start-time index parity (Codex)

Codex closed a still-current TS/Swift schema parity gap from the review
backlog.

Change:
- `src/core/db/migration.ts` now creates
  `idx_migration_log_state_started` on `migration_log(state, started_at)`.
- This matches the Swift schema in
  `macos/EngramCoreWrite/Database/EngramMigrations.swift`, including its
  repair migration for existing databases.
- The index supports pending/stale migration scans that filter by state and
  inspect start time, instead of relying on separate single-column indexes.

Verification:
- RED: `npm test -- tests/core/db-migration.test.ts` failed with
  `expected [ Array(54) ] to include 'idx_migration_log_state_started'`.
- GREEN: the same command passed 16 tests after the migration fix.
- Old-DB smoke: precreated a complete `migration_log` table without the
  compound index, opened it through `Database`, and observed
  `CREATE INDEX idx_migration_log_state_started ON migration_log(state,
  started_at)` in `sqlite_master`.
- Fixture determinism: regenerated `test-fixtures/test-index.sqlite` and
  inspected it to confirm the same index exists in the committed fixture DB.

