## 2026-06-06 — Codex project-move compatibility verification (Codex)

Codex verified the Codex project-move surface after the Claude/Qoder directory
encoding fix.

Conclusion:
- Codex does not use Claude-style cwd-encoded project directories. Active
  sessions live under `.codex/sessions`; archived sessions live under
  `.codex/archived_sessions`.
- TypeScript `src/core/project-move/sources.ts` and Swift
  `macos/EngramCoreWrite/ProjectMove/Sources.swift` both register `codex` and
  `codex-archived` as flat roots with no `encodeProjectDir`, so project move
  scans and patches literal path references in JSONL content but does not
  rename Codex directories.
- The Swift `CodexAdapter` also expands `.codex/sessions` to include
  `.codex/archived_sessions`.

Evidence:
- Read-only local corpus scan found 2,175 Codex rollout JSONL files, 2,165
  cwd-bearing sessions, zero non-absolute cwd values, and zero project-dir-like
  path layouts. Five archived sessions live directly under
  `.codex/archived_sessions`, which is still covered by the flat archived root.

Verification:
- `npx vitest run tests/core/project-move/sources.test.ts
  tests/core/project-move/orchestrator.integration.test.ts
  tests/core/project-move/review.test.ts` passed 50 tests.
- `xcodebuild test -project macos/Engram.xcodeproj -scheme EngramCoreTests
