## 2026-06-06 — Claude Code/Qoder project-dir encoding parity (Codex)

Codex closed the remaining known project-move compatibility gap for Claude
Code/Qoder project directory names.

Change:
- `src/core/project-move/encode-cc.ts` and
  `macos/EngramCoreWrite/ProjectMove/EncodeClaudeCodeDir.swift` now implement
  Claude Code's full encoder: replace every non-`[A-Za-z0-9]` UTF-16 code unit
  with `-`; if the encoded name exceeds 200 UTF-16 code units, use the first
  200 encoded units plus `-` plus `Math.abs(SYH(originalPath)).toString(36)`.
- Swift mirrors JavaScript UTF-16 behavior, including astral scalars becoming
  two `-` code units and the 32-bit wrapping hash.
- TS and Swift regression tests now cover exactly-200 paths, >200 truncation,
  base36 hash suffixes, underscore/space/dot replacement, and long emoji paths.

Evidence:
- Local Claude Code 2.1.165 bundle contains `Hj(H)` with
  `H.replace(/[^a-zA-Z0-9]/g,"-")`, `uUH=200`, and
  `Math.abs(SYH(H)).toString(36)`.
- Real-corpus replay of `~/.claude/projects` and `~/.qoder/projects` matched
  after allowing any cwd inside a project directory to encode back to the
  directory name. Claude Code: 39 cwd-bearing dirs checked across 88 total dirs,
  zero mismatches; Qoder: 7/7, zero mismatches. The longest real dir observed
  was 86 code units, so the >200 branch is covered by binary-derived synthetic
  tests rather than live corpus.

Verification:
- `npx vitest run tests/core/project-move/encode-cc.test.ts` passed 12 tests.
- `npx vitest run tests/core/project-move/*.test.ts
  tests/tools/project-mcp.test.ts` passed 17 files / 217 tests.
- `xcodebuild test -project macos/Engram.xcodeproj -scheme EngramCoreTests
  -destination 'platform=macOS' -only-testing:EngramCoreTests/EncodeClaudeCodeDirTests
  CODE_SIGNING_ALLOWED=NO` passed 13 tests.
- Selected Swift project-move tests
  (`EncodeClaudeCodeDirTests`, `SessionSourcesTests`, `OrchestratorTests`,
  `BatchTests`, `ReviewScanTests`, `ArchiveTests`, `UndoTests`) passed 98 tests.

