## 2026-06-06 — Project archive gitdir marker validation (Codex)

Codex closed a surviving low-priority project-migration review finding in
archive auto-categorization.

Root cause:
- Swift and TS archive suggestion logic treated any regular `.git` file as a
  valid worktree/submodule marker. Empty or malformed marker files could be
  auto-classified as `archived-done` instead of requiring an explicit `--to`
  category.

Change:
- Swift `Archive.suggestTarget` and TS `suggestArchiveTarget` now parse regular
  `.git` files as bounded 512-byte `gitdir:` markers.
- The resolved git metadata directory must contain `HEAD`; malformed or empty
  marker files fall through to the existing ambiguous-project path.
- Added Swift and TS regression tests for valid gitdir marker files and
  malformed marker files.

