## 2026-06-06 — MCP project_review Claude Code encoding parity (Codex)

Codex found and fixed a residual Claude Code compatibility gap after PR #51.

Root cause: Swift product project migration and TS reference code were fixed to
match real Claude Code project-dir encoding, but `macos/EngramMCP/Core/
MCPFileTools.swift` still had a private MCP-only `encodeCC()` that replaced
only `/` with `-`. This affects the read-only MCP `project_review` classifier:
for a migrated project like `/Users/test/work/CCTV_Admin`, the own Claude Code
dir is `-Users-test-work-CCTV-Admin`, but the stale helper expected
`-Users-test-work-CCTV_Admin` and classified own leftovers as `other`.

Fix:
- Updated MCP `encodeCC()` to match the Swift product encoder's UTF-16 code
  unit rule: every non-`[A-Za-z0-9]` code unit becomes `-`.
- Added MCP executable golden coverage:
  `testProjectReviewClassifiesClaudeCodeDirsWithNonAlnumEncoding`.

Verification:
- RED: the new test failed with `own: []` and both Claude Code files under
  `other`.
- GREEN: the same test passed after the MCP helper fix.
- Current compatibility spot-checks also passed: TS project-move/MCP/API
  compatibility tests (5 files / 88 tests) and Swift encoder tests (10 tests).

## 2026-06-06 — Project migration OpenCode SQLite compatibility (Codex)

Codex closed the remaining SQLite-backed project-move source gap.

Root cause: OpenCode sessions store cwd in
`~/.local/share/opencode/opencode.db`, table `session`, column `directory`.
Swift/TS project migration listed `.local/share/opencode` as a source root but
only scanned JSON/JSONL files via `findReferencingFiles`, so `project_move`
could commit while OpenCode rows still pointed at the old cwd. Review scans
also missed this because `.db` files are not text session files.

Fix:
- Added Swift `OpenCodeSQLiteProjectMove` helper in ProjectMove sources.
- Added TS better-sqlite3 helper in the project-move orchestrator and a
  read-only residual detector in `review.ts`.
- Live migration patches `session.directory` where it is exactly `oldPath` or
  under `oldPath/`; lookalikes such as `oldPath-lookalike` are intentionally
  untouched.
- SQLite matching checks `oldPath`, NFC, and NFD variants by UTF-8 byte
  identity before computing the replacement suffix. This avoids Swift
  `String` canonical-equivalence collapsing decomposed paths during variant
  generation.
- Dry-run counts OpenCode SQLite rows in the `opencode` per-source stats.
- Review reports residual OpenCode refs as virtual locators:
  `opencode.db::session:<id>:directory`.
- Compensation records the exact OpenCode session ids changed by the forward
  update and reverses only those ids, so rollback cannot corrupt rows that
  already belonged to the attempted destination path.

Verification:
- RED first: TS orchestrator integration showed `opencode` stayed 0/0 and
  Swift showed `session.directory` retained the old cwd.
- GREEN: `npm test -- tests/core/project-move` -> 16 files / 191 tests.
- GREEN: selected Swift `OrchestratorTests` + `ReviewScanTests` -> 30 tests.
- GREEN: `npm test` -> 127 files / 1516 tests.
- GREEN: `npm run lint`, `npm run build`, `npm run typecheck:test`,
  `git diff --check`.

