## 2026-06-03 — Multi-model review adjudication and fixes (Codex)

Codex adjudicated the Kimi/Gemini/MiniMax/Mimo review bundle against the
current `perf/transcript-paging` worktree and fixed the confirmed high-impact
items with focused regression coverage. The three existing review commits before
this pass only changed `CODE-REVIEW-ISSUES.md`; the Kimi report was pasted in
chat and was not a commit.

Implemented:
- TS correctness: OpenAI truncated embeddings are L2-normalized, parent cascade
  preserves subagent `tier='skip'`, `deleteSession` is transactional and removes
  vector/chunk/job rows, session project and metrics timestamp indexes were
  added, empty `indexed_at` values are backfilled, and today's parent count no
  longer wraps `start_time` in `datetime(...)`.
- TS stability/security: daemon shutdown uses live resource getters, MCP exit
  closes the DB, watcher indexing has a per-file in-flight lock, database
  statement wrappers avoid per-access function allocation, AI audit event bodies
  are sanitized before emission, Gemini JSON imports are capped, Antigravity cwd
  inference reads only the file head, sanitizer patterns cover common API keys,
  config parse failures warn, title timeout avoids `AbortSignal.timeout`, and
  `link_sessions` rejects protected system targets before writing. Project-move
  core now rejects non-absolute/protected system paths before any filesystem
  step; `lint_config` rejects unsafe cwd roots; FTS empty queries return
  directly instead of relying on SQLite parser fallback.
- Tooling: Vitest was upgraded to 4.1.8, `npm audit --audit-level=moderate` was
  added to CI, daemon was removed from coverage excludes, `export` now writes
  under `~/.engram/exports`, `hide_session` reports not-found, early MCP
  errors include `structuredContent`, Biome `noExplicitAny` is an error for
  production TS, Swift CI tests now run with code coverage enabled, Dependabot
  covers npm/GitHub Actions, and the CLI dispatcher now awaits dynamic imports
  with a top-level error handler instead of leaving unhandled rejections.
- Swift/macOS parity: migrations now add project/metrics indexes, metrics CHECK,
  trigram `insights_fts`, and `indexed_at` backfill; suggested-parent backfill
  avoids N+1 parent lookups; ClaudeCode adapter infers project from cwd;
  MCP search joins session rows in one query; handoff now respects `sessionId`
  and includes cost/duration/model/task prompt context; MCP schema validation
  enforces numeric minimum/maximum; OrderedJSON serializes non-finite doubles as
  null instead of crashing; get_session now streams JSONL/adapter transcripts and
  retains only the requested page; generic os_log wrappers and CoreWrite direct
  os.Logger callsites use private interpolation; SearchView cancels async search
  and embedding-status tasks before stale callbacks can publish results; hygiene
  returns an explicit degraded result instead of a false perfect score.
- Swift service follow-ups: Unix socket client reads/writes retry `EINTR`;
  `confirmSuggestion` now refreshes `link_checked_at`; snapshot upserts preserve
  existing `cwd` and message counts when a parse yields empty replacement data;
  migration audit notes are capped before DB insert; LLM non-2xx errors no
  longer echo upstream response bodies; transcript export/web redaction covers
  common PAT/AWS/npm/Slack/PEM token families; native project migration commands
  now log requested/finished/failed paths through `ServiceLogger`.
- Additional Swift review follow-ups: `SessionBatchUpsert` now wraps a batch in
  a savepoint so bare test callers and production callers share batch-scoped
  atomicity; startup emits explicit `backfill_inline` events for Swift's inline
  count/cost path; `MigrationLock` has a default 1h TTL and treats Darwin zombie
  holders as stale; iFlow lossy project-dir collisions are detected by scanning
  iFlow cwd records even when old/new encoded dirs are equal; Web UI transcript
  parser failures now return non-200 statuses; export leaf symlinks are covered
  by regression tests.
- Project-move/source filesystem hardening: `JsonlPatch.patchFile` now refuses
  symlink source files before read/rename and fsyncs the temporary replacement
  file before the atomic rename; `walkSessionFiles` reports FIFO/socket/device
  entries as `skipped_non_regular` instead of silently dropping them;
  `migration_log` has a `(state, started_at)` index on fresh and existing DBs;
  shared JSONL adapter discovery uses lstat-based directory/regular-file checks
  so direct-child adapters such as Cline do not traverse symlinked task dirs.
  TS `ClaudeCodeAdapter` now also derives `project` from `cwd`, keeping the
  adapter-parity fixture generator aligned with Swift's product behavior.
- UI/settings/security follow-ups: `LogStreamView` now stores and cancels its
  reload task for timer/filter changes; `AISettingsSection` and
  `DataSourceRow` suppress save/writeback while loading persisted values; Web UI
  Host validation now rejects malformed multi-colon loopback hosts instead of
  treating them as bare loopback.
- Title-regeneration follow-up: `regenerateAllTitles` now routes title
  generation through a testable helper that checks task cancellation before each
  title and again before DB writes, preserves the existing resilient per-session
  AI failure skip behavior, caps concurrent AI title calls at 4 by default, and
  emits coarse progress logs every 10 processed title contexts and at
  completion.
- Swift app concurrency follow-up: `DatabaseManager` is no longer globally
  `@MainActor`; it is an `@Observable` `@unchecked Sendable` read facade with
  the existing lock-protected pool, so views can capture it into
  `Task.detached` without relying on a source-comment-only `nonisolated`
  contract.
- Swift IPC sendability follow-up: `UnixSocketEngramServiceTransport` now uses
  checked `Sendable` conformance; the only remaining unchecked sendable helper
  in that file is the mutable `FdBox` wrapper that actually needs it.
- Swift app service-event follow-up: `AppDelegate.startServiceStatusObservation`
  now starts the status/event pump with `Task.detached`, keeping the event
  stream off the MainActor and hopping back only for `EngramServiceStatusStore`
  updates.
- Swift navigation race follow-up: `MainWindowView.navigateToSession` now tracks
  the latest palette-requested session id and ignores stale detached DB lookup
  completions, so a slower lookup cannot overwrite a newer session navigation
  or a direct `.openSession` notification.
- Swift session-list race follow-up: `SessionListView.loadSessions` now uses a
  monotonic load generation guard so the initial appear load, filter debounce
  reload, and action-triggered reloads cannot overwrite newer session/filter
  state when their detached DB reads complete out of order.
- MCP FTS transient-rebuild follow-up: keyword reads against `sessions_fts` and
  `insights_fts` now retry once after a short delay when SQLite reports the
  canonical FTS table is transiently absent during rebuild swap.
- Swift watcher/orphan follow-up: `SessionSnapshotWriter` now clears
  `orphan_status`, `orphan_since`, and `orphan_reason` after any successful
  authoritative snapshot handling, including same-content noop re-indexes. This
  closes the unlink+add/rename case where a session could remain hidden by MCP
  `orphan_status IS NULL` filters after the file reappeared unchanged.
- Swift startup dedup follow-up: `StartupBackfills.deduplicateFilePaths` now
  reparents confirmed and suggested children from duplicate session ids to the
  kept session id before deleting duplicate `file_path` rows, preserving parent
  links instead of letting the delete trigger clear them.
- Swift observability retention follow-up: startup retention now always logs a
  completion line with the pruned row count, including `0`, so the maintenance
  path is observable even when there is nothing to delete.
- Swift service test isolation follow-up: project-migration IPC pipeline error
  coverage now runs under `ServiceCoreTestHomeScope` with a temp HOME instead
  of constructing absent-source paths under the user's real home directory.
- Swift UI formatter follow-up: `TimelinePageView.formatDateLabel` now reuses
  static input/output `DateFormatter` instances instead of allocating a new
  formatter for every timeline group render.
- Swift Web UI observability follow-up: service startup now logs both
  `webUIEnabled=false` and `webUIEnabled=true` branches before the ready event,
  so enabled-by-settings startup has a breadcrumb before the health probe.
- Swift service log-category follow-up: `.writer` and `.ai` already had
  production callsites; `.ipc` now logs listener readiness and `.reader` now
  logs semantic/hybrid search degradation, so all declared service log
  categories are exercised by production code.
- Swift link-sessions symlink follow-up: native `linkSessions` no longer
  removes or replaces an existing link path. Matching symlinks are skipped,
  different symlinks and non-symlinks are reported as errors, and missing paths
  are the only paths created.
- Swift database file-security follow-up: `SQLiteFileSecurity` now chmods and
  then asserts DB/WAL/SHM siblings are owned by the current uid and mode 0600,
  keeping plaintext `migration_log` paths protected by an explicit startup
  invariant instead of a best-effort chmod alone.
- Swift project-path symlink confinement follow-up:
  `validateProjectPathConfined` now validates both the standardized caller path
  under `$HOME` and the symlink-resolved path under the symlink-resolved home,
  rejecting project move/archive/link targets that are textually inside home but
  resolve outside it. Sensitive-path checks also run against both path forms.
- Swift project-move errno follow-up: `OrchestratorError` now conforms to the
  `ProjectMoveError` envelope contract, and per-source dir rename failures
  preserve POSIX `errno=<code>` plus the strerror message in
  `DirRenameFailedError` details instead of surfacing only Foundation's
  localized text.
- Swift SQLite adapter accessibility follow-up: Cursor and OpenCode
  `isAccessible` now reuse a per-adapter actor-isolated
  `Phase4SQLiteDatabase` by db path, so startup orphan scans do not reopen the
  same shared SQLite database once per session/composer.

