## 2026-06-02 — Web UI pager O(N²)→O(N) lazy streaming (Claude)

First of the two deferred perf items from the review cleanup is DONE and merged:
PR #33 squash-merged to `main` as `685838e2`. Ultrareview (cloud, on the PR) = 0
findings.

What changed: added shared `JSONLAdapterSupport.windowedMessages(..., transform:)`.
When `limit` is set it streams line-by-line, skips `offset` PRODUCED messages
(post-transform, nils excluded — same unit as `applyWindow`), collects `limit`,
then STOPS reading → a paged read is O(offset+limit) parsed lines, not O(file).
When `limit` is nil it falls back to `readObjects`+`applyWindow`, byte-identical
to the old behavior — so indexer/export/MCP (all `limit: nil`) are unchanged, no
re-index. Routed through it: claude-code (+minimax/lobsterai via delegation),
qwen, iflow, qoder, commandcode, copilot, antigravity (CLI branch), codex (its
bespoke `readWindow` collapsed in and deleted).

NOT changed (by format, documented in CHANGELOG): kimi (multi-file + cross-line
turn/timestamp state), vscode (whole-session object), gemini/cline (whole-file
JSON), cursor/opencode (SQLite — future SQL LIMIT/OFFSET push-down). They parse
per page but don't re-read a growing JSONL tail.

Tests green: AdapterParity 24, MessageParser 20, EngramCoreTests 341,
EngramServiceCore 108, EngramMCPTests 58. Early-termination is proven physically
(oversized line past the window trips `.lineTooLarge` on a full read but a
windowed read ending before it succeeds), not just by message-count contrast.

STILL DEFERRED: item #2 — `SessionDetailView` whole-transcript load. Now it can
reuse this `limit` early-termination via `MessageParser.parse(offset:limit:)`;
the real fix is a transcript paging UI (a feature), not a silent truncating cap.

## 2026-06-02 — MCP fix + full Swift-product review/fix/cleanup (Claude)

Three things this session, all shipped: MCP repair, a comprehensive review, and
a fix+cleanup pass. Commits `b3510d22`, `77b1efab`, `fde4af83` pushed to `main`;
Developer ID release build `0.1.0 (738)` installed to `/Applications/Engram.app`
and relaunched (single app+service instance; `claude mcp list` → engram
Connected).

MCP root cause + fix:
- "engram MCP failed to connect" was NOT a Codex regression — Claude Code
  2.1.160 sends `protocolVersion: "2025-11-25"` in `initialize`, and
  `MCPStdioServer.supportedProtocolVersions` only allowed up to `2025-06-18`,
  so it hard-rejected with `-32602`.
- LESSON (applies to any MCP server, e.g. coding-memory too): per the MCP spec,
  on an unknown/newer requested protocol version the server must NEGOTIATE DOWN
  to its latest supported version, never error. EngramMCP now adds `2025-11-25`
  AND negotiates unknown versions to `latestSupportedProtocolVersion`.

Review + fixes:
- Full multi-agent review of the shipped Swift product (16 subsystems, security
  excluded) → `CODE-REVIEW-2026-06-02.md` (62 adversarially-verified findings).
- Fixed 53 in a parallel pass + closed residuals in a cleanup pass; 787 tests
  green (EngramCoreTests/EngramServiceCore/EngramMCPTests/EngramTests).
- Re-adjudicated every finding against current code (61 fixed, 5 by-design, then
  the last test-gap + search-debounce closed).

KNOWN DEFERRED (safe minimum in place, full fix = larger separate refactor):
- Web UI transcript pager re-parses the whole file per page → O(N²) paging.
  RESOLVED 2026-06-02 (PR #33 / `685838e2`) — see top entry. Lazy line-streaming
  window now in shared `JSONLAdapterSupport.windowedMessages`.
- `SessionDetailView` loads the whole transcript into memory (no parse limit).
  Now fully off-main + one-time per open (memory-only); full fix = transcript
  paging UI, not a silent truncating cap.

Deploy recipe used (faster than the full `build-release.sh` archive, still
notarizable identity): incremental `xcodebuild -scheme Engram -configuration
Release CURRENT_PROJECT_VERSION=<git rev-list --count HEAD> CODE_SIGN_STYLE=Manual
CODE_SIGN_IDENTITY="Developer ID Application: zhibing zhao (J25GS8J4XM)"
DEVELOPMENT_TEAM=J25GS8J4XM OTHER_CODE_SIGN_FLAGS="--timestamp" build`, then
`rm -rf /Applications/Engram.app && cp -R <DerivedData>/Release/Engram.app
/Applications/`, then `osascript quit` + `open`. Build number = git commit count.

