## 2026-05-30 — deep-dimension audit round 2 complete (Claude)

Chose option (a) from the prior resume point: a DEEPER 8-dimension
adversarially-verified audit of `main` (concurrency, GRDB txns, IPC, migration
idempotency, parsing/path-safety, UI races, ProjectMove, indexing lifecycle).
22 raw → 18 confirmed (≥2/3 skeptic lenses) → 16 deduped. All shipped as seven
focused, individually-verified, squash-merged PRs #26–#32 (CHANGELOG
`[Unreleased]` has the full per-issue detail):
- #26 pm-1 lock leak + pm-2 partial-patch (HIGH, project-move)
- #27 grdb_txn-1 writer-gate permit-leak deadlock (HIGH)
- #28 idx-2 startup-scan gate split + stale FTS test fix
- #29 mig-1 FK-orphan fatal migration + grdb_txn-2 snapshot savepoint
- #30 idx-1 periodic parent detection + idx-4 git pipe deadlock
- #31 ui-1..7 SwiftUI off-main reads + async ordering
- #32 ipc-3/4 + idx-5 + WebUI expectedPort (LOW service hardening)

Deferred as documented conscious tradeoffs (LOW severity, risk > value):
- **mig-2** FTS_VERSION-bump empty-search window — clean fix is a risky
  side-table-build + atomic-swap rewrite of the rebuild/drain path.
- **conc-1** per-client blocking readFrame on the cooperative pool — bounded by
  the 10s SO_RCVTIMEO once ipc-3 always arms it; offload is a transport refactor.

Verified clean (no fix): parsing/path-safety — MCP transcript reads DB-resolved
paths (ID lookup, not caller input), lint refs cwd-confined, JSONL readers skip
malformed/invalid-UTF-8 without crashing, regexes ReDoS-safe.

DURABLE LESSONS this round:
- **CI gap**: `swift-unit` runs only the `Engram` scheme (EngramCoreTests +
  EngramTests). It does NOT run `EngramServiceCoreTests` or `EngramMCPTests`. So
  service-core/MCP changes are only compile-gated by CI; run them locally with
  `-scheme EngramServiceCore` / `-scheme EngramMCP`. This gap let #19's stale FTS
  test slip into main. Backend (non-UI) PRs can merge on the 5 fast checks (no
  branch protection / required checks); only wait for ui-test-smoke on UI PRs.
- The grdb_txn-1 writer-gate bug also caused an INTERMITTENT hang in the existing
  `testCancelledQueuedWriteCommandDoesNotExecuteLater`; #27 fixed both.
- Two automated audit prompts hit an AUP cyber false-positive (the
  completeness-critic and a "path-traversal security auditor" agent). Reframe
  security-flavored reviews as ordinary defensive code review, or do them inline.
- TS test `npm run test:coverage` (the `typescript` CI job) is occasionally
  flaky on Swift-only PRs; `gh run rerun <id> --failed` clears it.

Resume point: round is complete. Natural next options if asked: (b) a post-merge
regression audit of #26–#32, (c) the deferred mig-2 side-table swap and/or the
conc-1 cooperative-pool offload, or (d) add EngramServiceCoreTests/EngramMCPTests
to CI (needs a socket/timing-test stability review first).

